add git config user.name to vagrant/jenkins.sh e.g. fix:
    *** Please tell me who you are.
    
    Run
    
      git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
      git config --global user.name "Your Name"
    
    to set your account's default identity.
    Omit --global to set the identity only in this repository.
    
    fatal: empty ident  <jenkins@precise64.(none)> not allowed
use requirements.txt
make sure tests/jenkins.sh and git-hooks/post-commit both get APPNAME from a variable
unless requirements change or override env var is set, do not rebuilt virtualenv each time
